## Frequently Asked Questions

### How does Riaz Counseling help teenagers manage panic attacks and anxiety?

Riaz Counseling helps teens manage panic attacks and anxiety by using evidence-based methods like cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT). Their therapists work one-on-one with young people to identify triggers, challenge fearful thoughts, and develop practical coping skills in a supportive mental health environment, ensuring a great fit between client and counselor.

### What therapy methods are offered for panic disorder in teens?

Riaz Counseling offers several effective therapy methods for teen panic disorder. Their primary approaches include cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT), a proven technique for anxiety, and Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR) for trauma-related issues. They also provide traditional talk therapy (psychotherapy) to improve overall mental health.

### Can families participate in counseling sessions at Riaz Counseling?

Yes, families are encouraged to participate in counseling at Riaz Counseling. They offer family therapy sessions to help improve communication, resolve conflicts, and create a healthier home environment. These sessions provide a safe space for all family members to learn how to support one another under professional supervision and consultation.

